<TEXT>
a small commercial plane with 20 people 
aboard made an emergency landing near the venezuelan border during a 
storm sunday killing four people and injuring 12 the government 
said 
the plane a canadianbuilt twin otter operated by the private 
domestic company aerotaca landed on a bank of the casanara river 
because of a driving rain said colombias civil aeronautics agency 
the report did not say what damage the plane suffered or how the 
four people died and it did not give the breakdown of passengers 
and crew a press report said all people aboard the twinengine 
plane were colombian 
among the passengers were colombian folk singer and composer 
arnulfo briceno as well as reporters and television cameramen 
invited by the stateowned company ecopetrol to retrace the route 
taken by simon bolivar during the final battles on colombian 
independence from spain 170 years ago said an agency spokesman 
the names of the other passengers and crew were were not 
immediately available and it was not known whether briceno was among 
the victims 
the plane was flying between bogota and tame an oil town 220 
miles east of the capital the spokesman said speaking on condition 
of anonymity 
a company source said the pilot reported the plane could not land 
in tame because of the heavy rain and was fly on to bucaramang the 
largest city in eastern colombia authorities declared the plane 
missing when it failed to reach its destination 
some colombian air force units searched for the plane but it was 
not immediately clear who spotted the aircraft 
</TEXT>
