<TEXT>
jose lopez rega a police corporal 
and amateur astrologer who rose to power after he became president 
juan domingo perons personal secretary died in jail of a heart 
attack he was 72 
lopez regas death was announced friday night by judge martin 
irurzuns office 
the son of spanish immigrants lopez rega was born oct 17 1916 
in buenos aires he tried a singing career and then became a 
policeman before being employed as a bodyguard for peron who was 
elected president in 1946 and then overthrown in a military coup in 
1955 
lopez rega renewed his acquaintance with peron in the mid 1960s 
when the ousted leader was living in exile in madrid he became 
perons personal secretary and returned to argentina with peron 
after the military dictatorship agreed to free elections 
peron was elected president in 1973 and he appointed lopez rega 
the minister of social welfare 
peron died july 1 1974 and his wife isabel who was vice 
president became chief executive lopez rega was a key adviser to 
her and gained wealth and power 
critics claim he helped set up the argentine anticommunist 
alliance a rightist deathsquad organization accused of dozens of 
killings 
isabel peron was ousted by an armed forces coup in 1976 and lopez 
rega fled argentina and went into hiding 
he was arrested in the united states and extradited to argentina 
in july 1986 to face charges of fraud and conspiracy 
earlier this year he was acquitted of fraud but remained in jail 
pending trial on charges stemming from his alleged connection to the 
anticommunist alliance 
</TEXT>
