israels military sunday lifted a weeklong 
curfew that confined 700000 palestinians to their homes in the gaza 
strip ending one of the longest restrictions imposed in the 
18month arab uprising 
also sunday 15yearold mohammed saeed shaweeshin died of a 
gunshot wound in the head suffered in a clash with soldiers saturday 
in gazas jabaliya refugee camp arab reports said an 
eightyearold boy also was killed in the stonethrowing 
confrontation 
officials at israels tel hashomer hospital near tel aviv where 
the teenager was taken for treatment declined immediate comment 
the army said it is checking the report 
shaweeshins death brings the toll to at least 515 palestinians 
killed since the revolt against israeli rule began in the occupied 
west bank and gaza strip twentytwo israelis have died in the 
violence 
some 4000 cars carrying palestinians left gaza after the curfew 
was lifted to take workers to their jobs in israel israel radio 
said 
but the restriction remained in jabaliya camp where 53000 
palestinians had to stay home 
the military imposed the curfew june 4 to control the population 
by issuing identity cards that workers will have to show to enter 
israel 
in the tel aviv suburb of petah tikva 150 peace activists 
demonstrated sunday against the towns plan to require that arab day 
laborers wait in a specially designated transit station on the 
outskirts 
