us sprint and science applications international corp an 84 
million contract to build a data network linking va offices and 
medical facilities nationwide according to telenet a sprint 
subsidiary that designed the system 
san diegobased saic is the prime contractor and will provide 
computer software and management systems for the integrated data 
communications utility while us sprint will provide network 
office and transmission equipment reston vabased telenet 
communications corp said friday 
the new system will serve 377 geographic locations including the 
172 va medical centers when it is fully installed in about two 
years 
the network will replace the vas data transmission systems and 
its benefits delivery system which serve about 80 million veterans 
dependents and survivors of deceased veterans telenet said 
at a cost to va of just over 84 million over 10 years the 
idcu will increase efficiency and result in cost savings to the va 
by enabling it to take advantage of new technology and new lower 
circuit rates telenet said 
