an unprecedented experiment in public education is 
about to begin with gov michael s dukakis expected to sign a bill 
monday that will let boston university take over the troubled school 
system in the city of chelsea 
the plan approved by the legislature after months of sometimes 
bitter discussion will link a public school system with one of the 
highest dropout rates in the state 17 percent to a worldclass 
university with all its financial and educational resources 
boston university will get the prestige of conducting an 
educational experiment never before tried in the united states one 
that will be watched closely and possibly duplicated by universities 
around the country 
one of the things i think wed like to encourage in this state 
is innovation and experimentation dukakis said at a news 
conference and theres no question this is innovative and 
experimental 
we have a bill which i think has real promise for the future of 
the schoolchildren in chelsea dukakis said its an experiment 
and like most experiments it is one that has to be tried before we 
know whether it will succeed 
under the plan bu will run the 3600student system for 10 years 
and pump in money from private donors and foundations for a variety 
of new programs including early childhood education counseling and 
nutritional services 
chelsea schools have been woefully underfunded according to 
officials in the largely hispanic workingclass city of 25000 
outside boston chelsea has seen its tax base shrink and faces cuts 
of about 28 million in next years school budget because of a 
state budget crunch 
