while orally promising to abide by state openmeeting laws had held 
up the bill and had put dukakis in a difficult position once the 
measure reached his desk 
local teachers unions and the american federation of teachers 
which endorsed dukakis in his bid for president last year had 
complained that the pact would allow bu to make decisions behind 
closed doors but a veto would have set up dukakis for an 
embarrassment since the legislature had passed the bill with enough 
votes to override 
on friday however the governor said he would sign the bill 
and also direct the state board of education to set up a monitoring 
panel to make sure bu abides by the openmeeting and publicrecords 
laws 
that move seemed to satisfy several factions that were 
practically at one anothers throats days earlier 
