turn over the sales proceeds to the government while keeping a small 
commission 
but in 1985 she used some of the hud money to cover a 37000 
shortfall in her business harrell told the times when several 
months passed without an inquiry from hud it became clear to her 
the department was so poorly run that it was unable to track the 
millions in dollars in payments due from escrow agents she said 
she took more money as much as 55 million by her estimate 
before anyone noticed investigators believe she bought 20 homes and 
nearly 40 automobiles for the needy 
she told the post in an interview published sunday that some of 
the money may have become mingled into improvements on her home 
that included a swimming pool a 2500 widescreen television and 
renovations to her basement 
but she said she used her home as a homeless shelter and 
therefore she could justify the expenses she said she now has 
transferred the home to hud in an attempt to offset her financial 
problems 
her scheme began to unravel last year she said when a hud 
official in the washington field office everett rothschild 
detected the diversion 
rothschild would not comment when contacted sunday but his 
attorney joseph scott was quoted by the post as saying 
rothschilds suspension was an outrage 
rothshcild is the person who came in and tried to do something 
about this scott said 
rothschild is chief of the property disposition division of the 
washington field office keating said rothschild was placed on leave 
without pay along with margaret white who heads the office robert 
warner director of housing management and charle womble a 
supervisory loan specialist 
harrell faces questioning by a grand jury in baltimore and says 
she is cooperating with investigators trying to track the diverted 
funds 
she told the times she was relieved her activities finally were 
out in the open 
christians arent perfect she was quoted as saying 
theyre just forgiven 
</TEXT>
